<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-30T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/11497:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-30T19:00:00+03:00">May
                                        30, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 1—7:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>622. My 621, May 30, 6 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d732fn16">Not
                                    printed.</note> From the Military Attaché to M. I. D. The fact
                                that the evacuation of Crete is actually in progress although known
                                in limited circles in Cairo has not yet attained any degree of
                                publicity here.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>